			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2020</a> paper:</span><br><i>Grammar-Based Testing for Little Languages: An Experience Report with Student Compilers</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/PhillipvanHeerden.html">Phillip van Heerden</a>, <a href="../profile/MoeketsiRaselimo.html">Moeketsi Raselimo</a>, <a href="../profile/KonstantinosSagonas.html">Konstantinos Sagonas</a>, <a href="../profile/BerndFischer.html">Bernd Fischer</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3426425.3426946">10.1145/3426425.3426946</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1b.html"><span class="tagM">T1B: Static Semantics</span></a><ul><li> The paper’s main contribution concerns static semantics, especially typing or constraint checking.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> It includes substantial tool support or infrastructure relevant for engineering/using languages.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4b.html"><span class="tagL">T4B: Horizontal Transformation</span></a><ul><li> It performs mapping/conversion/synchronization between representations (horizontal transformations).
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4c.html"><span class="tagL">T4C: Vertical Transformation</span></a><ul><li> It uses compilation/generation/refinement to derive executable artifacts (vertical transformations).
</li></ul></li></ul>
